To save data to localStorage in JavaScript, use the `setItem()` method. Here's an example:

```javascript
localStorage.setItem('key', 'value');
```

In this example, 'key' is the name of the item you want to store and 'value' is the data you want to save.

To read back data from localStorage in JavaScript, use the `getItem()` method. Here's an example:

```javascript
var value = localStorage.getItem('key');
```

In this example, 'key' is the name of the item you want to retrieve and 'value' will be the data that was stored under that key.
